
                        Section 2 - Notes
                         COPY Instruction

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for COPY instruction
    FROM ubuntu
    COPY testfile* /
    COPY mydir /images
    COPY --chown=10:20 mycert /
    CMD ["/bin/bash"]

2.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t copy . 

3.  Enter container and show files copied.

    $ docker run -it copy
    root@66f816799a3d:/# ls
    bin  dev home   lib   media mycert proc run  srv testfile1 tmp var
    boot etc images lib64 mnt   opt    root sbin sys testfile2 usr
    root@66f816799a3d:/# ls images
    image1  image2  image3
    root@66f816799a3d:/# ls -l mycert
    -rw-r--r-- 1 uucp dialout 0 Oct  7  2019 mycert
    root@66f816799a3d:/# exit 

    For mycert, uid (10) is uucp and gid (20) is dialout.

